Now begins the rehearsal of enmities between the signs, 520-535 already mentioned in verse 469. From the enmities of whole trigons we pass to the enmities of single signs. These are traced by Manilius to three sources: geometry (57 2-578), zoology (536-538), and the freedom of the will (539 sq.). a.
